Author-Name: Gadi Barlevy  
Author-Name: Derek Neal  
Title: Pay for Percentile 
Abstract:
 We propose an incentive scheme for educators that links compensation to
 the ranks of their students within comparison sets. Under certain
 conditions, this scheme induces teachers to allocate socially optimal
 levels of effort. Moreover, because this scheme employs only ordinal
 information, it allows education authorities to employ completely new
 assessments at each testing date without ever having to equate various
 assessments. This removes incentives for teachers to teach to a particular
 assessment form and eliminates opportunities to influence reward pay by
 corrupting assessment scales. Education authorities can employ separate
 no-stakes assessment systems to  track trends in scaled measures of
 student achievement. (JEL I21, I28, J33, J45)
