Author-Name: Daniel J. Benjamin  
Author-Name: Ori Heffetz  
Author-Name: Miles S. Kimball  
Author-Name: Alex Rees-Jones  
Title: What Do You Think Would Make You Happier? What Do You Think You Would Choose? 
Abstract:
 Would people choose what they think would maximize their subjective
 well-being (SWB)? We present survey respondents with hypothetical
 scenarios and elicit both choice and predicted SWB rankings of two
 alternatives. While choice and predicted SWB rankings usually coincide in
 our data, we find systematic reversals. We identify  factors--such as
 predicted sense of purpose, control over one's life,  family happiness,
 and social status--that help explain hypothetical choice controlling for
 predicted SWB. We explore how our findings vary by SWB measure and by
 scenario. Our results have implications  regarding the use of SWB survey
 questions as a proxy for utility. (JEL  D03, I31)
