Author-Name: Natalia Jimenez  
Author-Name: Juan A. Lacomba  
Author-Name: Francisco Lagos  
Title: The Hidden Advantage of Delegation: Pareto Improvements in a Gift Exchange Game 
Abstract:
 This paper analyzes the effect on performance and earnings of delegating
 the wage choice to employees. Our results show that such delegation
 significantly increases effort levels. Moreover, we observe a Pareto
 improvement, as the earnings of both employers and employees increase when
 employers delegate than when they do not. Interestingly, we also find that
 the employees' performance under delegation is higher than under
 nondelegation, even for similar wages. While there is strong evidence that
 behavior reflects strategic considerations, this result also holds for
 one-shot interactions. A possible nonstrategic motivation explaining the
 positive reaction to delegation is a sense of enhanced responsibility.
 (JEL J31, J33, J41)
